title: SFH learns about medical and funeral services in Shanghai (with photos)
content_text:
p>
    The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, today (October 22) 
    continued his visit to Shanghai. He called on the Director of the Shanghai 
    Municipal Health Bureau, Mr Xu Jianguang, this morning to learn more about 
    the food safety measures for Expo 2010 Shanghai China (Shanghai Expo). They 
    also shared their experiences in carrying out healthcare reform and tobacco 
    control measures in the two places. Dr Chow then visited the Shanghai Shenkang Hospital Development Centre and

met its Director, Dr Chen Jianping, to discuss problems facing the 
    healthcare reforms and services in both places. The Centre was set up by the 
    Shanghai Municipal Government in 2005 as a hospital management centre. Since 
    its establishment, the Centre has been working closely with Hong Kong's 
    Hospital Authority in experience sharing.  In the afternoon, Dr Chow visited the Affiliated Children's Hospital of 
    Fudan University with the aim of drawing experience from it for the later 
    establishment in Hong Kong of a medical centre of excellence in paediatrics.

establishment in Hong Kong of a medical centre of excellence in paediatrics. 
    The paediatrics hospital provides a full range of clinical, education and 
    research services, with 630 hospital beds and 28 clinical teaching rooms. It 
    is the teaching arm of the Department of Paediatrics of Fudan University, 
    providing training to postgraduates, undergraduates and graduate students, 
    as well as medical professionals. Dr Chow then met the Deputy Director-General of the Shanghai Municipal Civil 
    Affairs Bureau, Mr Wang Wanli, to learn about provision of funeral

Affairs Bureau, Mr Wang Wanli, to learn about provision of funeral facilities there. They also exchanged views on how to formulate policy and standards on funeral-related matters. Dr Chow yesterday visited the Shanghai Expo and toured the China Pavilion, Hong Kong Pavilion and Hong Kong's Urban Best Practices Area Exhibition. Ends/Friday, October 22, 2010
Issued at HKT 16:27
